Mix lemon juice, oil, onion and garlic in large re-sealable plastic bag. Place steaks in marinade. Seal bag and refrigerate 6 to 24 hours, turning bag occasionally. When ready to cook, season steaks with salt and coarsely ground pepper. Discard marinade. Spray grill rack with no-stick cooking spray. Heat grill. Cook jam, vinegar and onion powder in small saucepan over medium heat until jam is melted, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Place steaks on prepared grill. Cook 8 to 12 minutes or until desired doneness, turning once halfway through cooking time. To serve, top steaks with blackberry sauce. Sprinkle with fresh blackberries.